en_205344_0	Parliamentarian, Venerable Athuraliye Rathana Thera stated that if the leaders of the main political parties can come into an agreement, the country can be developed in 3 years.
en_205344_1	The first assembly of the Sri Lanka Jathika Maha Sabha convened by Venerable Athuraliye Rathana Thera, was held today at the Sadaham Sevana Dharmayathana in Rajagiriya.
en_205344_2	The assembly was convened with the intention of formulating a national policy on developing the country.
en_205344_3	Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa, former minister Basil Rajapaksa as well as UNP parliamentarian Wasantha Senanayake took part in the assembly.
en_205344_4	Our correspondents stated that a discussion was held between the Prime Minister and Venerable Athuraliye Rathana Thera.
en_205344_5	The Sustainable National Policy publication of the Sri Lanka Jathika Maha Sabha has also been presented to the Prime Minister.
